tnmMIB.description: Experimental MIB modules for tnm based agents.

tnmVersion.name: tnmVersion
tnmVersion.description: The version number of the tnm agent.

tnmTclVersion.name: tnmTclVersion
tnmTclVersion.description: The version number of the running Tcl interpreter.

tnmTclCmdCount.name: tnmTclCmdCount
tnmTclCmdCount.description: The nummber of Tcl statements evaluated so far.

tnmTrapDst.name: tnmTrapDst
tnmTrapDst.description: The host name of the trap sink host.

tnmTrapMsg.name: tnmTrapMsg
tnmTrapMsg.description: The description of the last trap create by this entity.

URL.name: URL
URL.description: A uniform ressource locator as defined in RFC 1738.

tnmHttpProxy.name: tnmHttpProxy
tnmHttpProxy.description: This variable specifies the proxy server. It must be of the form <name>[:<port>] where <name> is either a domain name or an IP address and <port> is the port number used to access the proxy server. The default port number is 80.

tnmHttpSource.name: tnmHttpSource
tnmHttpSource.description: Setting this variable will make tnm to download and source the document with the given URL. The agent will try to retrieve the document and sets the variable to the URL if this operations was successfull. Otherwise, the value will become an empty string.

tnmHttpError.name: tnmHttpError
tnmHttpError.description: This variable contains an error string is an http operation fails. An empty string signals that the last operation completed successfully.

tnmPeerTable.name: tnmPeerTable
tnmPeerTable.description: A (conceptual) table storing known tnm peers.

tnmPeerEntry.name: tnmPeerEntry
tnmPeerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the peer table.

tnmPeerTAddress.name: tnmPeerTAddress
tnmPeerTAddress.description: The address and port number of the peer agent.

tnmPeerAuth.name: tnmPeerAuth
tnmPeerAuth.description: The authentication information for this peer. This will usually be a community string until we get the final SNMPv2 decisions about the security model.

tnmPeerState.name: tnmPeerState
tnmPeerState.description: The current status of the peer as returned by the last status probe message.

tnmPeerLastChecked.name: tnmPeerLastChecked
tnmPeerLastChecked.description: The value of sysUpTime when the status of the peer was retrieved and written to tnmPeerState.

tnmPeerStatus.name: tnmPeerStatus
tnmPeerStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in the tnm peer table.

tnmElectionIndex.name: tnmElectionIndex
tnmElectionIndex.description: The (hopefully) unique index of this peer used by the bully election algorithm.

tnmElectionPanic.name: tnmElectionPanic
tnmElectionPanic.description: Reading this variable will start the panic algorithm on this peer. (We should use an inform request here.)

tnmElectionMaster.name: tnmElectionMaster
tnmElectionMaster.description: This variable will be set by a new master appearing on the scene. (We should use an inform request here.)

tnmEvalSlot.name: tnmEvalSlot
tnmEvalSlot.description: The index number of the first unassigned entry in the evaluation table. A management station should create new entries in the evaluation table using this algorithm: first, issue a management protocol retrieval operation to determine the value of evalSlot; and, second, issue a management protocol set operation to create an instance of the evalStatus object setting its value to underCreation(1). If this latter operation succeeds, then the management station may continue modifying the instances corresponding to the newly created conceptual row, without fear of collision with other management stations.

tnmEvalEntry.name: tnmEvalEntry
tnmEvalEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the evaluation table.

tnmEvalIndex.name: tnmEvalIndex
tnmEvalIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used for identifying instances of the columnar objects in the evaluation table.

tnmEvalValue.name: tnmEvalValue
tnmEvalValue.description: The value resturned by executing evalString.

tnmEvalStatus.name: tnmEvalStatus
tnmEvalStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in the evaluation table.
